Sure, here's a self-sufficient canvas drawing code in JavaScript that draws all the lines of a rugby pitch:

```javascript
// Define the size and position of the pitch
const pitchWidth = 70.0;
const pitchLength = 100.0;
const lineWidth = 4.0;
const width = pitchWidth + lineWidth * 2;
const height = pitchLength + lineWidth * 2;

// Create a canvas element
const canvas = document.createElement("canvas");
canvas.width = width;
canvas.height = height;
document.body.appendChild(canvas);

// Get the canvas context and set the line width
const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");
ctx.lineWidth = lineWidth;

// Draw the outline of the pitch
ctx.rect(lineWidth, lineWidth, pitchWidth, pitchLength);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the halfway line
const halfway = pitchLength / 2.0;
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, halfway + lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, halfway + lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the 22-metre line
const lineDistance = pitchLength - 22.0;
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, lineDistance + lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, lineDistance + lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the try lines
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, lineWidth);
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, pitchLength + lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, pitchLength + lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the 10-metre line
const tenMeters = 10.0;
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, tenMeters + lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, tenMeters + lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the 5-meter line in front of each try line
const fiveMeters = pitchLength - 5.0;
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, fiveMeters + lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, fiveMeters + lineWidth);
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth, pitchLength - lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth, pitchLength - lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();

// Draw the lineout lines
const lineoutDistance = 15.0;
ctx.moveTo(lineWidth + lineoutDistance, lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(lineWidth + lineoutDistance, pitchLength + lineWidth);
ctx.moveTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth - lineoutDistance, lineWidth);
ctx.lineTo(pitchWidth + lineWidth - lineoutDistance, pitchLength + lineWidth);
ctx.stroke();
```

This code should draw all the lines of a rugby pitch on a canvas element on the webpage. You can modify the values of `pitchWidth`, `pitchLength`, and `lineWidth` variables to adjust the size and style of the pitch lines if necessary.
